  Campaign Types
  <br>
  There are two main different types of campaign, Modules and original campaigns.
  Playing a module means playing a pre-written campaign out of a book. An original campaign is one written or adapted by your DM.
  Both can be fun experiences, though playing a module tends to mean a stricter adherence to the official ruleset for which the module was designed.
  <div class="field">
    <%=f.label :original_campaign %>
    <%= f.check_box :original_campaign %>
    <br>
    <%= f.label :module %>
    <%= f.check_box :module %>
  </div>

